Dallas Mavericks Beat Portland Trail Blazers 89-81 in NBA Playoff Series

-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 
2011-04-17T04:17:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-17/dallas-mavericks-beat-portland-trail-blazers-89-81-in-nba-playoff-series.html
The  Dallas  Mavericks defeated the
Portland Trail Blazers 89-81 in the first round of the National
Basketball Association playoffs.  The Mavericks have a one-game advantage in the Western
Conference best-of-seven series.  Dirk Nowitzki led the Mavericks with 28 points and 10
rebounds and Jason Kidd added 24 at American Airlines Center in
Dallas.  LaMarcus Aldridge was high scorer for the Trail Blazers with
27 points.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nancy Kercheval at 
 nkercheval@bloomberg.net  